title: Secrets of the Crime Museum   (Crime Channel  -  2008)
description:
TV : Crime : TV quality : English

Hidden away on the 1st floor of New Scotland Yard in Central London, the Crime Museum has quietly archived the tools, relics and instruments of killers, conmen and thieves for the last 130 years. It is not a museum that the public can visit easily and is open by invitation only - now Crime & Investigation Network has been granted access to film inside for a new 13-part series.

Presented by one of Britain's most experienced broadcasters, Nick Ross gives viewers exclusive access to the world's oldest museum of crime.

Note: Part 5 is missing!


Enjoy and Seed!!
